        <h2>Types of Mortgage Refinance</h2>

        <h3>Rate-and-Term Refinance</h3>
        <p>Replaces your current mortgage with a new one at a different rate and/or term. Best for lowering your interest rate, switching from ARM to fixed-rate, or changing loan length (30-year to 15-year).</p>

        <h3>Cash-Out Refinance</h3>
        <p>Borrow more than you owe, receiving the difference in cash. Best for home improvements (can increase home value), debt consolidation, or major expenses. Rates are typically 0.125-0.25% higher than rate-and-term.</p>

        <h3>Streamline Refinance</h3>
        <p>Simplified refinance for existing FHA, VA, or USDA loans with minimal documentation. Best for quick rate reduction without appraisals—VA IRRRL and FHA Streamline are the most common.</p>

