          <p><strong>Break-Even = Closing Costs ÷ Monthly Savings</strong><br/>
          Example: $6,000 closing costs ÷ $200 monthly savings = 30 months (2.5 years). If you plan to stay longer, refinancing likely makes sense.</p>
